Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, governor of Sokoto State Aminu Waziri Tambuwal, minister of youth and sports, Sunday Dare and the wife of the Bayelsa State governor, Mrs. Gloria Douye Diri are to receive the Elite Exclusive Magazine awards. The ceremony, slated for May 24, 2022, in Abuja, will be part of the activities marking the 5th anniversary of the magazine. In a statement issued by the magazine’s publisher, Mr. Mbuotidem Ubom, he said the “nominees were chosen by members of the public via online based on their track record of service to humanity.” Ubom said Osinbajo was nominated as Public Servant of the Year; Mrs Gloria Douye Diri and Mrs. Martha Udom Emmanuel as First Ladies of the Year; Sunday Dare, Mrs. Paullen Tallen and Hon Rotimi Amaechi as Ministers of the Year, while Pastor Umo Eno is Elite Man of the Year. Other recipients are a governorship aspirant in Akwa Ibom state, Pastor Umo Eno, Senators Ali Ndume and Gershom Bassey as Senators of the Year; Boboye Oyeyemi and Prof. M.N. Sambo of NHIS for Elite Award in Leadership; Hon. Adebo Ogundonyin and Chief Sherrif F.O. Obrevori as Speakers of the Year; Tope Shonubi of Sahara Energy and Ikechukwu Nnamdi of Medallion Group as Business Persons of the Year. Also, Prof. Ekele Bisallah Ahmed of the University of Abuja Teaching Hospital and Prof. Ememabasi Bassey are nominated as Health Persons of the Year; Obong Patrick Udofia, International President of Mboho Mkparawa Ibibio and Prof Benjamin Okaba, President of Ijaw National Congress as Life Time Achievers, while Professors Ndaeyo Ukpabio and Abdallah Uba Adamu as Vice Chancellors of the Year.